The take command will pick up an item (or items) on the space the player is standing on and places them into the player's inventory.

Usage:
  take

If no parameter is given, take will get the top object that can be taken and place it in the player's inventory.

Example:
  You pick up the table.

If no object can be taken, that will be stated.

Example:
  You can't pick up a wood floor.

By default, take is bound to the comma (,) key with no parameters.

  See Also: [help]pickup[/help]
  See Also: [help]get[/help]
  See Also: [help]bind[/help]
